>Isn't possible
If there is sentient life out there, it's almost a guarantee that they look at least vaguely similar to us. Manipulating limbs, locomotion limbs, and all the usual sensory organs are guaranteed. Since 4 limbs is the most effective method of early locomotion, and then locomotion and manipulation late stage, odds are that they'll be bipedal. Because Earth's gravity is about as high as it can be while still allowing for the escape of the atmosphere, any space fairing people is almost guaranteed to be either our size, or taller (while still being lighter). Developing without a snout is possible, but unlikely as the snout is almost guaranteed to be developed early stage, and would need a reason to shorten/be lost lately stage. Two sexes are also quite likely, as they developed as the perfect mix between spreading out genetic code to defend against disease, and efficient reproduction.
It won't be big tiddied werewolf gf, but the odds of attractive alien women existing is very high if we ever encounter extraterrestrials.
